data: {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"toolu_01GHQzyKTPQzYKRXrXjwQMJF","content":"The `AGENTS.md` file contains the following main sections:\n\n*   **[Identity]**: System identity and source code location.\n*   **[Rules]**: Security, confidentiality, and data verification (Ashby) protocols.\n*   **[Writing Quality Gate]**: Style and formatting requirements for responses.\n*   **[Environment]**: Repository locations and installed software stack.\n*   **[Tools \u2014 three kinds]**: Overview of Amp built-ins, API tools, and Browser tools.\n*   **[Browser \u2014 computer use]**: Detailed CLI commands and authentication workflows for the headless browser.\n*   **[Slack messaging \u2014 CRITICAL]**: Instructions for replying to users and uploading files.\n*   **[API access]**: Usage instructions for the `call` helper and sub-agent management.\n*   **[Cross-persona dispatch]**: Delegation of tasks to specialist agents (legal, eng, etc.).\n*   **[API tools index]**: Directory of available integration tools (financial, recruiting, search, etc.).\n*   **[Finance domain]**: High-level guidance for balance checks.\n*   **[Data routing]**: Source mapping for historical vs. live financial data.\n*   **[Slack files]**: Handling of auto-downloaded and remote Slack attachments.\n*   **[Staking]**: Specific queries and tools for various staking platforms.\n*   **[Token aggregation]**: Mapping of tickers to specific chain assets (HYPE, ETH, etc.).\n*   **[Coinbase Prime]**: Accounting logic for balance components.\n*   **[Defaults]**: Standard assumptions for queries regarding funds, assets, and timeframes.\n*   **[Reconciliation]**: Definitions for holdings, liquidity, and performance metrics (MOIC).\n*   **[Reference]**: Core metadata, fund names, and database table identifiers.\n*   **[Dashboard blocks]**: Syntax for rendering interactive UI components (tables, charts, KPIs).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019ce04c-e99b-77f6-b18f-185af7d122dc"}

